**Abstract:**
Major essay dated January 22, 1998 titled "On Truth and Decision" critiquing the reduction of knowledge to contemplation. Proposes alternative based on "exposure" with dramatic-narrative structure. Analyzes Aquinas on statements, arguing he wrongly privileges them as only truth-bearing speech acts. Develops perlocutionary primacy over illocutionary effects. Concludes: "Believing in God is finding oneself exposed to God and in interaction with him."

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay; see 98-JAN-3-1 variant. Central to exposure epistemology.

